verses.verse: (For the choir director. A Psalm of David. A Song.) There will be <S%H1747>silence<s%> before Thee, [and] <S%H8416>praise<s%> in <S%H6726>Zion,<s%> O <S%H430>God;<s%> And to Thee the <S%H5088>vow<s%> will be <S%H9608>performed.<s%>
O Thou who dost <S%H8085>hear<s%> <S%H8605>prayer,<s%> To Thee <S%H3605>all<s%> <S%H1320>men<s%> <S%H935>come.<s%>
<S%H5771>Iniquities<s%> <S%H1396>prevail<s%> <S%H4480>against<s%> me; As for our <S%H6588>transgressions,<s%> Thou dost <S%H3722>forgive<s%> them.

How <S%H835>blessed<s%> is the one whom Thou dost <S%H977>choose,<s%> and <S%H7126>bring<s%> <S%H7126>near<s%> [to Thee], To <S%H7931>dwell<s%> in Thy <S%H2691>courts.<s%> We will be <S%H7646>satisfied<s%> with the <S%H2898>goodness<s%> of Thy <S%H1004>house,<s%> Thy <S%H6918>holy<s%> <S%H1964>temple.<s%>

By <S%H3372>awesome<s%> [deeds] Thou dost <S%H6030>answer<s%> us in <S%H6664>righteousness,<s%> O <S%H430>God<s%> of our <S%H3468>salvation,<s%> Thou <S%H4009>who<s%> art the <S%H4009>trust<s%> of <S%H3605>all<s%> the <S%H7099>ends<s%> of the <S%H776>earth<s%> and of the <S%H7350>farthest<s%> <S%H3220>sea;<s%>
Who dost <S%H3559>establish<s%> the <S%H2022>mountains<s%> by His <S%H3581>strength,<s%> Being <S%H247>girded<s%> with <S%H1369>might;<s%>
Who dost <S%H7623>still<s%> the <S%H7588>roaring<s%> of the <S%H3220>seas,<s%> The <S%H7588>roaring<s%> of their <S%H1530>waves,<s%> And the <S%H1995>tumult<s%> of the <S%H3816>peoples.<s%>

And they who <S%H3427>dwell<s%> in the <S%H7117>ends<s%> [of the earth] <S%H3372>stand<s%> in <S%H3372>awe<s%> of Thy <S%H226>signs;<s%> Thou dost make the <S%H1242>dawn<s%> and the <S%H6153>sunset<s%> <S%H7442>shout<s%> for <S%H7442>joy.<s%>

Thou dost <S%H6485>visit<s%> the <S%H776>earth,<s%> and cause it to <S%H7783>overflow;<s%> Thou dost <S%H7227>greatly<s%> <S%H6238>enrich<s%> it; The <S%H6388>stream<s%> of <S%H430>God<s%> is <S%H4390>full<s%> of <S%H4325>water;<s%> Thou dost <S%H3559>prepare<s%> their <S%H1715>grain,<s%> for <S%H3651>thus<s%> Thou dost <S%H3559>prepare<s%> the earth.

Thou dost <S%H7301>water<s%> its <S%H8525>furrows<s%> <S%H7301>abundantly;<s%> Thou dost <S%H5181>settle<s%> its <S%H1417>ridges;<s%> Thou dost <S%H4127>soften<s%> it with <S%H7241>showers;<s%> Thou dost <S%H1288>bless<s%> its <S%H6780>growth.<s%>
Thou hast <S%H5849>crowned<s%> the <S%H8141>year<s%> with Thy <S%H9186>bounty,<s%> And Thy <S%H4570>paths<s%> <S%H7491>drip<s%> [with] <S%H1880>fatness.<s%>
The <S%H4999>pastures<s%> of the <S%H4057>wilderness<s%> <S%H7491>drip,<s%> And the <S%H1389>hills<s%> <S%H2296>gird<s%> themselves with <S%H1524>rejoicing.<s%>

The <S%H9221>meadows<s%> are <S%H3847>clothed<s%> with <S%H6629>flocks,<s%> And the <S%H6010>valleys<s%> are <S%H9400>covered<s%> with <S%H1250>grain;<s%> They <S%H7321>shout<s%> for <S%H7321>joy,<s%> <S%H637>yes,<s%> they <S%H7891>sing.<s%>
